   <refnamediv>

<refname>get_total_thread</refname>

<refpurpose>Get the total number of threads running in the parallel region.</refpurpose>

</refnamediv>

    <refsynopsisdiv>

<title>Syntax</title>

<synopsis>a = get_total_thread(Void)</synopsis>

</refsynopsisdiv>
   <refsection>

<title>Arguments</title>


<variablelist>


<varlistentry>

<term>Void</term>


<listitem>

<para>No arguments needed.</para>

</listitem>

</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>

<term>a</term>


<listitem>

<para>Output argument (returns total number of threads)</para>

</listitem>

</varlistentry>

</variablelist>

</refsection>
    <refsection>

<title>Description</title>

<para></para>

<para>This function returns the total number of threads running in the parallel region. </para>


<para>
This function inturn calls the omp_get_num_threads in C.
</para>

</refsection>
   <refsection>

<title>Examples</title>

<programlisting role="example">a=get_total_thread()</programlisting>

</refsection>

</refentry>